explanation: No additional symbols are required. print_perf_warnings has no parameters (signature: static void print_perf_warnings(void)), so it cannot violate the MISRA rule that a function parameter shall not be modified. Local variables (newline_needed) and calls to other functions (e.g. MHD_is_feature_supported, fprintf, printf) do not affect whether this function modifies its own parameters. Therefore no further symbols are needed to determine compliance with this specific rule.
